# Daily Log â€” Dec 23

## Focus

AWS fundamentals and IAM security model.

## Key Learnings

- Cloud abstracts infrastructure
- Regions and AZs enable availability
- IAM is the primary cloud security boundary

## What Could Go Wrong?

- Root account misuse
- Over-permissive IAM policies
- Long-lived credentials leakage

## How to Defend

- Use IAM users with least privilege
- Prefer roles over users
- Enable MFA

## Tradeoffs

- Convenience vs security
- Fine-grained IAM vs management complexity
